parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Takata airbag inflator can cause serious injury or death in the event of a crash. The lack of available parts and lengthy repair times can leave vehicles unrepaired, putting drivers and passengers at risk.
symptoms: Failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash
no notification of the recall
parts not available for repair
lengthy repair times
and lack of communication from dealerships and manufacturers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag to deploy in a crash can cause serious injury or death.
symptoms: Airbag failure to deploy in a crash
resulting in injuries to drivers and passengers.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the VSC system can cause the vehicle to suddenly brake or lose steering control, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The VSC warning light comes on
the vehicle suddenly brakes or loses steering control
the vehicle jerks or lurches
the headlights dim
and an audible beep can be heard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to be difficult to control, leading to accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The steering feels loose or difficult to turn
the steering makes a clicking sound
the power steering capabilities are lost
and the battery light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent power loss can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle suddenly loses power
the power steering capabilities are lost
and the battery light comes on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly and uncontrollably
often without warning
and may crash into other vehicles
objects
or buildings. The driver may experience difficulty stopping the vehicle
and the brakes may not respond as expected.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The erratic behavior of the traction control system can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and injuries, potentially resulting in fatalities.
symptoms: The VSC Trac sensor lights turn on and off
and a grinding noise is heard when the traction control system auto-engages and disengages. This can occur on sharp turns or off-ramps
even when the roadways are not slick or wet.
